current implementation of `decl_macro` seems to have some issues, as shown in this example ([playground](https://is.gd/bm7zng)):\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#![feature(decl_macro)]\r\n\r\nmacro macro_ {\r\n    () => {\r\n        #[derive(Debug)]\r\n        struct CreatedStruct;\r\n\r\n        impl From<()> for CreatedStruct {\r\n            fn from(_: ()) -> CreatedStruct {\r\n                CreatedStruct\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    };\r\n}\r\n\r\nmacro_!();\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    println!(\"{:?}\", CreatedStruct);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected this to compile and just print out \"`CreatedStruct`\" (from its derived `Debug` implementation), but it throws the following errors instead:\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror[E0425]: cannot find value `CreatedStruct` in this scope\r\n  --> <anon>:19:22\r\n   |\r\n19 |     println!(\"{:?}\", CreatedStruct);\r\n   |                      ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ not found in this scope\r\n   |\r\nhelp: possible candidate is found in another module, you can import it into scope\r\n   | fn main() use CreatedStruct;\r\n\r\nerror[E0046]: not all trait items implemented, missing: `from`\r\n  --> <anon>:8:9\r\n   |\r\n8  | /         impl From<()> for CreatedStruct {\r\n9  | |             fn from(_: ()) -> CreatedStruct {\r\n10 | |                 CreatedStruct\r\n11 | |             }\r\n12 | |         }\r\n   | |_________^ missing `from` in implementation\r\n...\r\n16 |   macro_!();\r\n   |   ---------- in this macro invocation\r\n   |\r\n   = note: `from` from trait: `fn(T) -> Self`\r\n\r\nerror: aborting due to previous error(s)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat's strange because our example should be equivalent to this ([playground](https://is.gd/gxKlyK)):\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nmacro_rules! macro_ {\r\n    () => {\r\n        #[derive(Debug)]\r\n        struct CreatedStruct;\r\n\r\n        impl From<()> for CreatedStruct {\r\n            fn from(_: ()) -> CreatedStruct {\r\n                CreatedStruct\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    };\r\n}\r\n\r\nmacro_!();\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    println!(\"{:?}\", CreatedStruct);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhich works just fine.\r\n\r\nThe scoping issue is likely caused by whatever is causing #42337, but I'm not sure what is happening with the trait implementation.\r\n\r\nCC @jseyfried", "closed_by": {"login": "r3c0d3x", "id": 18088837, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE4MDg4ODM3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/18088837?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/r3c0d3x", "html_url": "https://github.com/r3c0d3x", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/r3c0d3x/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/r3c0d3x/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/r3c0d3x/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/r3c0d3x/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/r3c0d3x/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/r3c0d3x/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/r3c0d3x/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/r3c0d3x/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/r3c0d3x/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/42448/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/42448/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}